data.title: James Lockwood (Connecticut politician)
data.text:
American politician

For other people named James Lockwood, see James Lockwood.

James Lockwood (April 21, 1683 â€“ May 5, 1769) was a member of the Connecticut House of Representatives from Norwalk, Connecticut Colony. He was the youngest son of Ephraim Lockwood and Mercy St. John and the brother of Eliphalet Lockwood.[2][3]

Lockwood served in the following sessions of the House:

May 1721

May 1722

October 1723

October 1724

May 1726

May 1727

May 1729

May and October 1732

May 1733

May and October 1735

May 1738

October 1739

May and October 1740

October 1742

May 1746

October 1748

October 1749

October 1751

He was appointed a justice of the peace by the General Assembly from 1744 to 1756.[2]
